The police on Thursday arraigned a 44-year-old driver, Olumamuywa Adeoya, in a Karmo Grade I Area Court, Abuja, for allegedly faking his own kidnap and deceiving his friend into paying N350,000 as ransom. <img class="size-full wp-image-1243908 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=640%2C355&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police" width="640" height="355" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?w=740&amp;ssl=1 740w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=300%2C166&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=260%2C144&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=200%2C111&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=560%2C310&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Adeoya, who resides in Karamajiji Area, Abuja, is charged with two counts of criminal breach of trust and cheating. The Prosecution Counsel, Mrs Ijeoma Ukagha, told the court that the complainant, Adebesin Daniel of Plot 20b Kucgiko Estate Bwari, Abuja reported the matter at the Life Camp Police Station, Abuja, on Aug. 27 Ukagha alleged that on Aug. 23 at about 5. 30 p.m. the defendant called the complainant, pleading for his assistance. The prosecutor alleged that the defendant told the complainant that he was abducted alongside one of his sons on the Kaduna-Abuja Express road. She said the defendant pleaded with the complainant to help him pay the ransom of N350,000 with a promise to pay back upon his release. Ukagha added that during police investigation, the defendant confessed to the crime, while efforts made to recover the money, failed. The offence, she said, contravened the provisions of sections 312 and 322 of the Penal Code. The defendant pleaded not guilty. The Presiding Judge, Alhaji Inuwa Maiwada, admitted Adeoya to bail in the sum of N50, 000 with one surety in like sum. Maiwada adjourned the case until May 6 for hearing. Vanguard The police on Friday arraigned a conman, Nna Peter, who allegedly hynotised a business woman and stole N540, 000, in a Karmo Grade I Area Court, Abuja. April 5, 2019 In "News" A Karmo Grade I Area Court, Abuja, ordered that ab businessman, Obinna Igwe, accused of N1.1 million visa fraud, be remanded in prison, pending police investigation. May 19, 2019 In "News" A Grade 1 Area Court, Karmo, Life Camp, Abuja, on Thursday admitted a 35-year-old driver, Emmanuel Adaba, to N10, 000 bail for alleged criminal intimidation. August 12, 2016 In "News"